.TH CHADDR-PROFILE 5 "June 2026" "chaddr @VERSION@" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
chaddr-profile \- chaddr address profile file format
.SH DESCRIPTION
A
.I chaddr
profile is a plain-text file that declares how to discover the current IP
addresses of a host and which resources must be checked or updated when those
addresses change. Profiles are read by
.BR chaddr (1).
.PP
Each file is a sequence of
.BR key: value
lines. Keys are case-insensitive. Empty lines and lines beginning with
.B #
are ignored, except for special
.B # option
directives (see below). A trailing backslash
.B \(rs
at the end of a physical line continues the line on the next line (shell-style
continuation).
.SH FILE LOCATION
Profile files have no required filename extension. By default they live in
.IR ~/.config/chaddr/profile/ .
Override the directory with the
.B CHADDR_PROFILE_DIR
environment variable. Example profiles ship in
.IR /usr/share/chaddr/profile/
when installed from a package, or in
.I profile/
in a source checkout. On first run, an empty user profile directory is seeded
from those examples.
.SH STRUCTURE
Profiles contain, in order:
.IP \(bu 3
An optional
.B header
(before the first
.B from:
or
.B type:
line).
.IP \(bu 3
An optional
.B from
block that resolves current addresses.
.IP \(bu 3
One or more
.B type
blocks, each describing a resource
.B chaddr
can diagnose, renew, or manually update.
.PP
A profile may contain multiple
.B type:
blocks. Each block starts with
.B type: \(laNAME\(ra
and continues until the next
.B type:
or
.B from:
line or end of file.
.SH HEADER
Header fields appear before the first
.B from:
or
.B type:
line.
.TP
.B description: \(laTEXT\(ra
Short human-readable label shown in the GUI profile list.
.TP
.B version: \(laTEXT\(ra
Optional version string shown in the GUI profile list.
.TP
.B addr-history: \(laADDRS\(ra
Whitespace-separated historical IPv4 and/or IPv6 addresses. IPv4 and IPv6 are
detected automatically. These addresses are treated like spare
.BR \-\-old-ip
values when matching old IPs in
.BR hosts (5)
entries and BIND zone files during diagnose and apply.
.SH FROM BLOCK
The optional
.B from
block tells
.B chaddr
how to discover the current primary addresses for the profile.
.TP
.B from: resolve
Use DNS to resolve a hostname.
.TP
.B resolve: \(laHOSTNAME\(ra
Hostname to resolve. Aliases:
.BR host: ,
.BR name: .
.PP
Example:
.PP
.RS
.nf
from: resolve
resolve: relay.example.com
.fi
.RE
.SH CLI OPTIONS IN PROFILES
Lines of the form:
.PP
.RS
.B # option \-\-flag
.RE
.PP
attach extra CLI flags to the following
.B type:
block. At the very beginning of a file (before any header,
.B from:
or
.B type:
line), such lines register global CLI options for the profile.
.PP
Credentials and secrets are normally read from
.IR chaddr.conf ;
profile
.B # option
lines are mainly for per-block flags required by handlers.
.SH RESOURCE TYPES
Each resource block begins with
.B type: \(laNAME\(ra
where
.I NAME
is one of the supported types below (case-insensitive).
.SS aws elastic ip
Diagnose and renew (reallocate) an AWS Elastic IP associated with an EC2
instance.
.TP
.B region: \(laREGION\(ra
AWS region ID or short alias. Aliases include
.IR sg1 ,
.IR kr1 ,
.IR hk1 ,
.IR jp1 ,
.IR jp2 ,
.IR au1 ,
.IR us1 ,
and
.IR us2 .
.TP
.B instance: \(laID\(ra
.TP
.B instance_id: \(laID\(ra
Optional EC2 instance ID. When omitted, the handler searches running instances
in the configured region.
.PP
Requires AWS credentials in
.IR chaddr.conf .
.SS aliyun elastic ip
Diagnose and renew (reallocate) an Aliyun Elastic IP.
.TP
.B region: \(laREGION\(ra
Aliyun region ID or alias (
.IR cn1 ,
.IR cn2 ,
.IR cn3 ,
.IR sg1 ,
.IR hk1 ,
etc.).
.TP
.B instance: \(laID\(ra
.TP
.B instance_id: \(laID\(ra
Optional ECS instance ID. When omitted, the handler searches running instances.
.PP
Requires Aliyun credentials in
.IR chaddr.conf .
.SS registered nameserver
Diagnose and manually apply IP changes to registered nameservers (Namecheap).
.TP
.B api: namecheap
Namecheap API (required).
.TP
.B ns: \(laHOSTS\(ra
Comma-separated nameserver hostnames, for example
.IR ns1.example.com ,
.IR ns2.example.com .
.TP
.B domain: \(laDOMAIN\(ra
.TP
.B ns_domain: \(laDOMAIN\(ra
Optional parent domain. When omitted, the domain is derived from the first
nameserver hostname.
.PP
Requires Namecheap API credentials in
.IR chaddr.conf .
.SS hosts file
Diagnose and manually apply IP changes in a local
.BR hosts (5)
file.
.TP
.B path: \(laFILE\(ra
Path to the hosts file (for example
.IR /etc/hosts ).
.TP
.B host: \(laNAMES\(ra
.TP
.B hosts: \(laNAMES\(ra
Optional comma-separated hostnames to limit which lines are considered. When
omitted, all lines matching spare/old IP addresses are updated.
.SS zone file
Diagnose and manually apply IP changes in a BIND zone file.
The legacy type name
.B bind db
is still accepted.
.TP
.B path: \(laFILE\(ra
Path to the zone database file.
.TP
.B record: \(laNAMES\(ra
.TP
.B name: \(laNAMES\(ra
Optional comma-separated record names to limit which A records are updated.
.SH ACTIONS BY TYPE
.TP
.B Diagnose
All supported types.
.TP
.B Renew (reallocate)
.B aws elastic ip
and
.B aliyun elastic ip
only.
.TP
.B Apply (manual IP change)
.B registered nameserver ,
.BR hosts file ,
and
.BR zone file .
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
.RS
.nf
# chaddr example profile
description: Example relay
version: 1
addr-history: 198.51.100.4 2001:db8::1 \\
  203.0.113.10

from: resolve
resolve: relay.example.com

type: aws elastic ip
region: us-east-1

type: aliyun elastic ip
region: cn-hangzhou

type: registered nameserver
api: namecheap
ns: ns1.example.com, \\
   ns2.example.com

type: hosts file
path: /etc/hosts

type: zone file
path: /var/cache/bind/db.example.com
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR chaddr (1),
.BR hosts (5),
.BR named (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Lenik &lt;chaddr@bodz.net&gt;
